<subSubSection id="E89536ECFFFBFFA4FD6AA173FCC105C0" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFBFFA4FD6AA173FCC105C0" blockId="20.[714,1243,1089,1769]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
DIAGNOSIS: Members of 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FB9AA172FBF004AE" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[1047,1116,1149,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FB9AA172FBF004AE" box="[1047,1116,1149,1172]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have filiform male antennae; central fascia of the forewing thin and medially and dorsally narrowed; male genitalia with hook-shaped uncus, transtilla thin, platelike, saccus medially projected, costa of valva strongly sclerotized with medial and distal projections, sacculus large, rounded, aedeagus slender with spinular processes distally; and female genitalia having lamella antevaginalis sclerotized, rounded; ductus bursae thin, long without a colliculum and the corpus bursae ovate without a signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E89536ECFFFBFFA5FD6AA30EFF1502DC" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFBFFA5FD6AA30EFED2012B" blockId="20.[714,1243,1089,1769]" lastBlockId="21.[103,632,221,1417]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
DISCUSSION: All species of 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FBBEA30EFBD40622" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[1075,1144,1537,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FBBEA30EFBD40622" box="[1075,1144,1537,1560]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(except 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FD47A310FCB2060C" box="[714,798,1567,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firmata">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FD47A310FCB2060C" box="[714,798,1567,1590]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">firmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are united by four synapomorphies: male antenna filiform (character #0-0), saccus medially projected (#23-2), dorsal edge of sacculus vertically sclerotized (#28-1), and lamella antevaginalis two doughnutlike structures without a seta (#37-2). The basal clade comprising 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FC26A3DDFC5C06D3" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[939,1008,1746,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FC26A3DDFC5C06D3" box="[939,1008,1746,1769]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FBB6A3DDFB1A06D3" box="[1083,1206,1746,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firmata">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FBB6A3DDFB1A06D3" box="[1083,1206,1746,1769]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">T. firmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is supported by one synapomorphy: transtilla large, platelike (#22-1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFAFFA5FF09A418FF1502DC" blockId="21.[103,632,221,1417]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Stephens (1831) proposed the genus 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FDBFA417FDDB0115" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[562,631,280,303]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FDBFA417FDDB0115" box="[562,631,280,303]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by separating it from 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FE1CA43AFDD40176" authority="Treitschke" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" box="[401,632,309,332]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chesias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE1CA43AFE410176" box="[401,493,309,332]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Chesias</emphasis>
Treitschke
</taxonomicName>
based on differences of the palpi, wing pattern and host plant (fir or juniper). Viidalepp (
<bibRefCitation id="C41E1896FFFAFFA5FFFDA482FF01019E" author="Tartu Riikliku" box="[112,173,397,420]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="54 - 84" refId="ref10193" refString="1980. Geometrid moths of the genus Thera Steph. in the fauna of the USSR (Lepidoptera). Tartu Riikliku ulikooli Toimetised 13 (516): 54 - 84. [in Russian with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">1980</bibRefCitation>
) defined the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FE7EA482FD94019E" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[499,568,397,420]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE7EA482FD94019E" box="[499,568,397,420]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: saccus tender and round; costa and sacculus of valva distinct; ductus bursae membraneous; and sterigma sclerotized. Choi (
<bibRefCitation id="C41E1896FFFAFFA5FE66A4EAFD8401C6" author="Nat" box="[491,552,485,508]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 242" refId="ref9826" refString="1997. The moths of Borneo: family Geometridae, subfamilies Sterrhinae and Larentiinae. Malay. Nat. J. 51: 1 - 242." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
) redefined the monophyly of the genus using 11 synapomorphies and listed four uniquely derived characters: costa of valva with a medial projection; cucullus large; and cornuti on vesica fewer and arranged in a crown shape. About 12 species of 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FEE3A79AFE1F0296" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[366,435,661,684]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FEE3A79AFE1F0296" box="[366,435,661,684]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known and they occur widely throughout the Holarctic region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E89536ECFFFAFFA5FF09A7E2FEF605B3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFAFFA5FF09A7E2FEF605B3" blockId="21.[103,632,221,1417]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FF09A7E2FF56033E" box="[132,250,749,772]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firmata">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FF09A7E2FF56033E" box="[132,250,749,772]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">T. firmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has seven autapomorphies: vertex distinct with whitish scales (character #1- 1), discal dot of forewing united to the costal part of antemedial line (#9-1), costa of valva with a distal expansion (#26-1), cornuti on vesica large and spinular and grouped into one-patch (#34-1, #35-1), and ductus bursae sclerotized (#48-1). The species 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FE65A6B5FDF003EB" box="[488,604,954,977]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firmata">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE65A6B5FDF003EB" box="[488,604,954,977]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">T. firmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is placed at the basal node of 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FE20A6D7FE5E03D5" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[429,498,984,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE20A6D7FE5E03D5" box="[429,498,984,1007]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the successive weighting approach (
<figureCitation id="38B479E2FFFAFFA5FE48A6FAFDBA0436" box="[453,534,1013,1036]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[129,167,1572,1593]" captionTargetBox="[203,1108,219,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[201,1111,214,1550]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 61. One cladogram derived from successive weighting approach using NONA. See fig. 60 for generic abbreviations and symbols. Each node number is indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5461664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5461664/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">fig. 61</figureCitation>
), but as a member of 
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE8CA11DFE230413" box="[257,399,1042,1065]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Heterothera</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="38B479E2FFFAFFA5FE2DA11DFE420413" box="[416,494,1042,1065]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[164,202,1599,1620]" captionTargetBox="[227,1150,218,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-12@16.[226,1154,214,1577]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 60. Strict consensus cladogram derived from unweighted analysis using NONA. Abbreviations: C Cidaria, D Dysstroma, P Plemyria, Pe Pennithera, Pd Paradysstroma, Pr Praethera, Ps Pseudodysstroma, H Heterothera, T Thera, Di Diathera. Plus signs (+) indicate a taxon or node that produces the polytomy in the consensus cladogram; asterisks (*) indicate taxa that have ambiguous taxonomic positions." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5461662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5461662/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">fig. 60</figureCitation>
). The status of this species was first discussed by Pierce (
<bibRefCitation id="C41E1896FFFAFFA5FFFDA142FF03045E" author="In A. Seitz &amp; Die Grossschmetterlinge der Erde" box="[112,175,1101,1124]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="216 - 219" refId="ref10045" refString="1914. Geometridae. In A. Seitz (ed.), Die Grossschmetterlinge der Erde - Die Palaearktischen Spanner. 1 (IV): 216 - 219. Stuttgart: Verlag A. Kernen." type="journal article" year="1914">1914</bibRefCitation>
). He distinguished it from 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FE64A142FD82045E" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[489,558,1101,1124]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE64A142FD82045E" box="[489,558,1101,1124]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on structures of the genitalia. Later, Viidalepp (
<bibRefCitation id="C41E1896FFFAFFA5FF20A188FF4604A4" author="Tartu Riikliku" box="[173,234,1159,1182]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="54 - 84" refId="ref10193" refString="1980. Geometrid moths of the genus Thera Steph. in the fauna of the USSR (Lepidoptera). Tartu Riikliku ulikooli Toimetised 13 (516): 54 - 84. [in Russian with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">1980</bibRefCitation>
) moved it to 
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE1AA187FDB304A5" box="[407,543,1160,1183]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FE1AA187FDB704A5" box="[407,539,1160,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Pennithera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pennithera</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
on the basis of two apomorphies: indistinct sacculus and shortly bipectinate male antenna. However, Choi (
<bibRefCitation id="C41E1896FFFAFFA5FF7BA1D0FE9F04CC" author="Nat" box="[246,307,1247,1270]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 242" refId="ref9826" refString="1997. The moths of Borneo: family Geometridae, subfamilies Sterrhinae and Larentiinae. Malay. Nat. J. 51: 1 - 242." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
) subsequently combined it with 
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FF21A1F2FEED052E" box="[172,321,1277,1300]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Heterothera,</emphasis>
using three synapomorphies: apical streak of forewing absent, anellus lobe expanded, and saccus flat and broad. In the present analysis, 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FE01A05AFE4C0556" box="[396,480,1365,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firmata">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE01A05AFE4C0556" box="[396,480,1365,1388]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">firmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is again associated with 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFAFFA5FE83A07DFEFF05B3" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" box="[270,339,1394,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFAFFA5FE83A07DFEFF05B3" box="[270,339,1394,1417]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Thera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
